Title: Demystifying the Black Box: Explainable AI (XAI) for Sensor-Based Ecosystem Health Predictions using SHAP
The Core Idea: Pehle se trained Random Forest model par SHAP algorithm chalana taake hum har ek individual water site ke liye ye dekh sakein ki kis environmental factor ne model ko "Healthy" ya "Degraded" predict karne par majboor kiya.

Special Library: Iske liye hamein Colab mein pip install shap karna hoga.

Desi Presentation Summary (Kia Kiya Aur Kse Kiya):
1. Data Aur Model:

Humne wahi 1,000 environmental sites wala tabular data use kiya (pH, Dissolved Oxygen, Nitrates, etc.) aur us par Random Forest Classifier ko train kiya.

2. XAI (SHAP) Kaunsa Use Kiya Aur Kyun?

Tool: TreeExplainer from SHAP library.

Kyun Kiya: Yeh algorithm game theory par kaam karta hai. Ye har ek feature (jaise Dissolved Oxygen) ko ek SHAP Value deta hai. Agar value positive ho, to iska matlab us feature ne model ko "Healthy Ecosystem" ki taraf dhaka diya. Agar value negative ho, to usne "Degraded" ki taraf dhaka diya.

3. Visual Plots (Jo Professor ka dil jeet lenge):

Hum do tarah ke plots generate karenge bina kisi PCA ke:

SHAP Summary Plot: Ye poore dataset ka ek hi screen par nichod dikha deta hai ke high/low features ka model par kya impact tha.

SHAP Waterfall/Force Plot (Individual Sample Analysis): Kisi ek makhsoos site ko pakad kar uska poora post-mortem karke dikhayega ke "Is specific pond mein oxygen kam thi aur nitrates zyada the, isliye model ne ise Degraded kaha."
